Noticed @the_x2y2 has an Anti-Phishing Code feature for emails sent to users. That's really smart and considerate for protecting users from phishing emails.
Other marketplaces like @opensea w/ email notifications should learn from that. https://t.co/49C4UaFHIq

HD wallets only sign msg/txns. That isolates access of seedPhrases/pvtKeys from DApps or connected devices hence to protect wallet accounts.
But, using HD wallets doesn't guarantee the safety of assets. Misuse still puts assets in danger. Should DYOR & not sign unknown msg/txn. https://t.co/TBzLTIZJAa

So LooksRare was focused on their tokenomics at launch was a good decision for the timing. They gained market when OpenSea was unable to use and then improve their product.

However, x2y2 launch was nothing like LooksRare.

x2y2 is too much focused on their token right now rather than the product itself.
LooksRare was not a ready product when it was launched but the timing was right, OpenSea constantly went down and many complaints from the users.

Now they want you to list valuable NFTs to claim $x2y2 airdrop, and their official audit is not published.
